-- Eight People at F1 Race Treated for Burns After Williams Fire
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-05-13T17:14:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-13/eight-people-at-f1-race-treated-for-burns-after-williams-fire.html
Eight people were taken to hospital
after suffering burns at Formula One’s  Spanish Grand Prix , when
a fire broke out in the Williams team garage, a police official
said by phone.  The fire started as Williams staff toasted victory by the
team’s driver Pastor Maldonado at Montmelo, near Barcelona.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
